      <li><b>Prizer-Painter PA family since 1880 / BlueStar 2002+</b>, independent hand-built manufacturer</li>
      <li><b>1,000+ color program</b>, factory-matched panel service (4-10 week lead)</li>
      <li><b>30" single + double wall oven</b>, common with matched BlueStar range pairing</li>
      <li><b>$89 residential diagnostic</b>, waived when you authorize the repair</li>
    </ul>
  </div></section>

  <BrandBranchesGrid />

  <section class="trust-bar"><div class="wrap"><span>BHGS #A49573 · Insured</span><span>Same-day in 5 SoCal counties</span><span>Residential diagnostic $89 · waived with repair</span></div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>BlueStar, independent family hand-built Pennsylvania</h2>
    <p>Prizer-Painter Stove Works is a family-owned Pennsylvania manufacturer with heritage dating to 1880. The BlueStar brand specifically launched in 2002 as Prizer-Painter's entry into the pro-grade residential cooking-appliance market, positioned as an independent hand-built alternative to the conglomerate-owned pro brands (Wolf/Sub-Zero Group, Viking/Middleby, Thermador/BSH). Each BlueStar unit is built to order at the Reading Pennsylvania facility, which is why LA customers who specified BlueStar during kitchen renovation remember waiting several weeks for factory delivery rather than picking up off a showroom floor.</p>
    <p>BlueStar's signature product differentiator is the 1,000+ color program. Where most pro brands offer stainless and a handful of finish options, BlueStar offers 1,000+ colors from a specified program plus custom color matching to any hex value a customer specifies. The color is baked into the exterior panel at factory, not a field-applied finish. In LA, this makes BlueStar popular at bold-design kitchens where the range + wall oven + hood becomes a visual focal point rather than a neutral background.</p>
    <p>For service economics, the independence from conglomerate parts networks means BlueStar parts run exclusively through Prizer-Painter Pennsylvania distribution, common service parts 3-7 day lead, specialty color-panel parts 4-10 week lead reflecting factory batch production.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>BlueStar wall oven models we service</h2>
    <div class="model-grid">
      <div class="model-card"><h3>BlueStar 30" single wall oven</h3><p>Built-in single-cavity wall oven in 1,000+ color options. Cavity cutout matches standard 30" wall oven dimensions; dedicated 240V circuit. Service: bake element, convection fan, control board, sensors, door hardware.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>BlueStar 30" double wall oven</h3><p>Stacked dual-cavity configuration, upper + lower independent elements + sensors, shared primary control. Matches common LA custom-kitchen column spec when paired with BlueStar range below.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Color-matched panel service</h3><p>Exterior color-panel replacement via Prizer-Painter Pennsylvania factory. 4-10 week lead depending on specific color availability. Document color code from interior plate at diagnostic.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Interior mechanical service</h3><p>Bake element, convection fan motor, sensors, control board, door hardware, doesn't affect exterior color panels, runs at standard BlueStar service economics.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Matched range + wall oven pairing</h3><p>LA BlueStar installs typically include a matched BlueStar range in the same kitchen. Shared Prizer-Painter parts chain supports combined service dispatch.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Self-clean cycle service</h3><p>Pyrolytic self-clean door-lock motor, thermal sensor, cycle firmware. Service patterns similar to mainstream wall oven architecture.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Common BlueStar wall oven faults</h2>
    <p><b>Bake element failure</b>, commercial-grade BlueStar element lasts 8-12 years typical LA residential use. Replacement $380-$620.</p>
    <p><b>Convection fan motor wear</b>, bearings develop play over years. Replacement $420-$680.</p>
    <p><b>Control board lockout</b>, factory reset resolves some; replacement $540-$880 when not.</p>
    <p><b>Temperature sensor drift</b>, cavity off-setpoint. Replacement $280-$440.</p>
    <p><b>Self-clean door-lock motor</b>, lock engagement failure at cycle start. Replacement $280-$460.</p>
    <p><b>Door hinge wear</b>, hinges develop play over years of thermal cycling. Replacement $320-$520.</p>
    <p><b>Color-panel exterior damage</b>, factory-matched replacement required. Quoted individually; 4-10 week Pennsylvania lead time.</p>
    <p><b>Double wall oven per-cavity service</b>, upper or lower only element + sensor work. $420-$780.</p>
  </div></section>

